  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x201C;Collaboration of UNICORN Psycho-social Support Center and its partner for SOGIE-based violence data</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">(1) To build data management and service capacities of UNICORN and its partner LGBTI organizations. 
(2) To create strong SOGIE-based violence database in Myanmar.  
(3) To provide psycho-social support services for victims of SOGIE-based violence in targeted areas. 
(4) To raise awareness of SOGIE-based violence to relevant government service-providers and stakeholders.  
(5) To evaluate and learn from the project; and plan for the future</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">. More qualified service providers from CSO with enhanced data management and service provision skills. 
2. Strong and systematic SOGIE-based violence database; and evidence-based community actions in Myanmar. 
3. LGBTIs who experience SOGIE-based violence in remote areas will be able to access more psychosocial services provided by UNICORN and its partners. 
4. Government agencies and civil society actors will take SOGIE-based violence issues seriously and provide the survivors necessary psycho-social services more efficiently. 
5. Project stakeholders will be more aware of the impacts of the project; and CAN-Myanmar staffs will be able to learn lessons from the project and plan their best for future activities.</narrative>
  </description>
